trend_summary: Tree-dominated suburbs gradually infill: new housing pockets, small commercial strips and a widened highway emerge, nibbling forest edges. Despite incremental sprawl, revegetation along the river and a rehabilitated quarry offset some loss. Overall, the area retains a medium-density suburban profile with modest but steady development pressure.
notable_changes: East-side highway widened and additional ramps constructed, improving regional access.
Commercial/industrial blocks expand south of the new interchange, replacing former woodland.
Fresh residential cul-de-sacs appear in the central valley, tightening housing grid.
Riverfront corridor gains thicker tree canopy and recreational path development.
Mid-eastern quarry clearing visible mid-series is progressively revegetated by the final frame.
